Thanks [~GergelyNovak] for the patch.
Agree that 1000 ms may not enough, given the sleep time in the worst case could reach to 900 ms.
{noformat}
    for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
      values = cache.values();
      if (values.size() > maxSize) {
        Thread.sleep(100);
      } else {
        assertFalse("fileInfo1 should have been evicted",
          values.contains(fileInfo1));
        return;
      }
    }
{noformat}
However, 10 secs may not be necessary. Can we set to 5000 ms instead?
